Sending SMS Text Messages response model
account[name]
data.description: the name for the new account

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][address]
data.description: new billing address

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][card_number]
data.description: credit card number

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][card_type]
data.description: type of credit card one of visa, master, american_express, or discover.

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][city]
data.description: new billing city

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][country]
data.description: new billing country, e.g. "United States", "Canada", "Mexico", "United Kingdom", etc...

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][first_name]
data.description: first name on credit card

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][last_name]
data.description: last name on credit card

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][month]
data.description: credit card expiration month

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][verification_value]
data.description: credit card verification number

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][year]
data.description: credit card expiration year

data.name: account[payment_profiles_attributes][0][zip]
data.description: new billing postal code

data.name: billing_type
data.description: the type of billing for this account either, existing or new, when new is selected additional payment profile options are required.

data.name: number
data.description: this is the receiving number, where you would like phone calls to be forwarded once received by the tracking number.

data.name: account_id
data.description: the account_id to grant this user access.

data.name: role
data.description: how the user can access the account, 'admin', 'report_manager', 'report_viewer'

data.name: position
data.description: A numeric value to indicate how this source should be evaluated with respect to all other sources. Lower values have higher precedence.

data.name: ref_pattern
data.description: A pattern to match on the referring website for matching the current visitor. e.g. document.referrer.  This should be a valid regular expression without the leading / and trailing /

data.name: url_pattern
data.description: A pattern to match on the current website location for the current visitor. e.g. window.location  This should be a valid regular expression without the leading / and trailing /

data.name: user[email]
data.description: email address for user

data.name: user[first_name]
data.description: first name for user

data.name: user[last_name]
data.description: last name for user

data.name: user[password]
data.description: password for user
Request paramaters are sent via an HTTP POST and should be URL Encoded.

data.description: the full number to purchase, this is the phone_number from the search API

data.name: conversion
data.description: a boolean flag (1 or 0) to indicate whether the call resulted in a sale.

data.name: sale_date
data.description: when a sale occurred as a result of this call.

data.name: score
data.description: a number between 1 and 5 to indicate the quality of the call.

data.name: service_rep_name
data.description: The name of the person who handled the call.

data.name: value
data.description: a numeric value to represent, the total worth of the call in dollars.
Triggers allow you to define how to react when receiving a text message. Should we auto respond with a message, forward the message to another phone, send an email etc...

data.name: country_code

data.name: from
data.description: tracking_number_id, the ID of the tracking number e.g. TPN...

data.name: msg
data.description: the text message to send, limited to 160 characters

data.name: status
data.description: a status call back is a web request we can send you after the message has been delivered. e.g. http://example.com/your-web-service

data.name: to
data.description: destination phone number, the digits of the phone number e.g. +1dddddddddd
